sequenceDiagram
    participant Deploy as deploy.sh<br/>(Init Container)
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as rhods-operator<br/>(KfDef Controller)
    participant Components as Platform Components<br/>(Dashboard, NBC, ModelMesh, etc.)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSProm as OpenShift Prometheus<br/>9091/TCP HTTPS
    participant Targets as Metrics Targets<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant BB as Blackbox Exporter<br/>9114/TCP HTTPS
    participant AM as Alertmanager<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PD as PagerDuty API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DMS as Dead Man's Snitch<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant SMTP as SMTP Relay<br/>SMTP/TLS

    rect rgb(220, 235, 250)
        Note over Deploy,Components: Flow 1: Platform Bootstrap Deployment
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Create namespaces<br/>Auth: SA Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>Deploy: Namespaces created<br/>(redhat-ods-applications,<br/>redhat-ods-monitoring,<br/>rhods-notebooks)

        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply namespace labels<br/>(pod-security, monitoring)
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply Network Policies
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply RBAC (SCC bindings)
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Install Dashboard CRDs<br/>(OdhApplication, OdhDocument,<br/>OdhQuickStart, OdhDashboardConfig)

        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply KfDef CRs (x8)<br/>Auth: SA Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: KfDef CR events
        Operator->>Operator: Load odh-manifests tarball<br/>(file://)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create component Deployments<br/>Auth: SA Bearer Token
        K8sAPI-->>Components: Deploy components

        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Apply ISV tiles + ConsoleLink
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Deploy Prometheus stack manifests
        Deploy->>K8sAPI: Generate & apply secrets<br/>(openssl rand)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 235, 220)
        Note over Prom,SMTP: Flow 2: Monitoring Pipeline (Managed Service)
        Prom->>OSProm: Federation scrape<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)<br/>Encryption: TLS (service CA)
        OSProm-->>Prom: haproxy, controller_runtime,<br/>container, kubelet, kube metrics

        loop Every scrape interval
            Prom->>Targets: Scrape component metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: None, Encryption: None
            Targets-->>Prom: Metrics response
        end

        BB->>Components: Health check probes<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS, 8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
        Components-->>BB: Probe response

        Note over AM,SMTP: Alert Routing (3 tiers)
        Prom->>AM: Fire alert<br/>(SLO burn-rate breach)
        AM->>PD: Critical SRE alert<br/>Auth: Service Key<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+
        AM->>DMS: Heartbeat (Watchdog)<br/>Auth: URL-embedded token<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+
        AM->>SMTP: User notification<br/>(PVC usage alerts)<br/>Auth: SMTP credentials<br/>Encryption: TLS
    end
